PHASE 3: ANALYSIS
================================================================================

Commands run:
  python3 researcher/analyze_csv.py ... --plots -o ~/Downloads/studentai/output/
  python3 researcher/visualize.py ... (multiple invocations, see plots below)
  python3 -c "... pandas / scipy analysis ..."  (inline scripts)

--- RQ1 Analysis ---

GenAI usage bucketed: Low (<3h), Mid (3–12h), High (>12h)

  Group summary:
    Bucket        n       Trad Hours  Post GPA  GPA Change
    Low (<3h)   15,146    11.88       3.336     +0.190
    Mid (3–12h) 22,750    11.40       3.366     +0.220  ← peak
    High (>12h) 12,104    10.02       3.335     +0.189

  Correlations:
    Traditional hours ↔ Post GPA:  r = +0.1377  p = 5.22e-210
    GenAI hours       ↔ Post GPA:  r = -0.0186  p = 3.19e-05
    GenAI hours       ↔ Trad hrs:  r = -0.1574  p = 1.27e-274

  ANOVA (Post GPA across buckets): F = 22.863, p = 1.19e-10

  GPA change by major:
    Arts:       +0.197
    Business:   +0.194
    Humanities: +0.198
    Medical:    +0.201
    STEM:       +0.217  ← highest

--- RQ2 Analysis ---

  Correlations with Anxiety:
    Perceived_AI_Dependency ↔ Anxiety:  r = +0.3076  p ≈ 0
    Weekly_GenAI_Hours      ↔ Anxiety:  r = +0.2691  p ≈ 0

  Anxiety by institutional policy:
    Actively_Encouraged:    mean = 4.119
    Allowed_With_Citation:  mean = 4.122
    Strict_Ban:             mean = 4.886  ← significantly higher

  Kruskal-Wallis (Anxiety across policies): H = 667.70, p = 1.02e-145

  Burnout (High %) by policy:
    Actively_Encouraged:    23.8%
    Allowed_With_Citation:  23.8%
    Strict_Ban:             29.8%  ← highest

--- RQ3 Analysis ---

  Tool Diversity ↔ Skill Retention:  r = +0.1970  p ≈ 0

  Retention by Prompt Engineering Skill:
    Beginner:     mean = 71.101  sd = 12.668
    Intermediate: mean = 75.825  sd = 12.431
    Advanced:     mean = 82.054  sd = 12.534  ← 11-point gap

  ANOVA (Retention by Prompt Skill): F = 3012.13, p ≈ 0

  Retention by Tool Diversity:
    1 tool:  72.59
    2 tools: 72.95
    3 tools: 76.42
    4 tools: 79.41
    5 tools: 79.81  ← monotonic increase, +7.2 pts total

  Retention interaction (Prompt Skill × Policy):
                     Encouraged  With Citation  Strict Ban
    Beginner            71.47        71.28        70.07
    Intermediate        76.20        75.88        75.10
    Advanced            82.35        82.14        81.39
    (Strict Ban penalty: ~0.9–1.4 pts, dwarfed by 11-pt skill gap)

================================================================================
PHASE 4: RESULTS (Chat Report)
================================================================================

Presented structured research report covering:
  - Data inventory and descriptive statistics
  - RQ1: Non-linear (inverted-U) relationship between GenAI use and GPA;
          displacement effect confirmed (r = -0.16)
  - RQ2: AI dependency is strongest predictor of anxiety (r = +0.31);
          counterintuitive finding that strict bans INCREASE anxiety/burnout
  - RQ3: Prompt engineering skill dominates retention (11-pt gap, F=3012);
          tool diversity adds monotonic benefit (r = +0.20)

